revision.text:
'''Archaeology of Afghanistan''' has revealed many historical findings, particularly on the ancient civilizations present in [[Central Asia]]. The world's oldest-known oil paintings, dating to the 7th century AD, were found in caves in Afghanistan's [[Bamiyan Valley]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/22/us-afghan-paintings-idUSISL26042420080422|title=World's oldest oil paintings in Afghanistan|publisher=Reuters|date=22 April 2008|accessdate=16 August 2015}}</ref>

Several sites of significance to the [[Kushan Empire]] have been discovered in Afghanistan.<ref>{{cite book|last=Stark|first=Miriam T.|authorlink1=Miriam Stark|title=Archaeology of Asia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=z4_bT2SJ-HUC&pg=PA335|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|year=2005|page=335|isbn=978-1405102131}}</ref>

