'''Piet Chielens''' (born 1956) a Belgian writer, translator and curator. He is coordinator of the [[In Flanders Fields Museum]] in [[Ypres]] (Ieper) in Belgium.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=N4EcAAAAIBAJ&sjid=_1cEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6887,2377707&dq=piet-chielens&hl=en "Britain Looks To Burying An Ugly Part Of Its Past" - Victoria Advocate]</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/1999/nov/11/firstworldwar.uk "Saving Private Byers" - The Guardian]</ref> He is also artistic director of ''Vredesconcerten Passendale'' (''[[Passendale|Passchendaele]] Peace Concerts'').<ref>[http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-4682954/Coope-Boyes-Simpson-harmonic-convergence.html "Coope, Boyes & Simpson: harmonic convergence" - Goliath]</ref>
Chielens was born in [[Reningelst]]. He is co-author, with [[Julian Putkowski]], of ''Unquiet Graves / Rusteloze Graven Guide: Execution Sites of the First World War in Flanders''.
