{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 340 |organ = SC |date = 25 October |year = 1973 |meeting = 1,750 |code = S/RES/340 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/340(1973) |for = 14 |abstention = 0 |against = 0 |subject = UN Emergency Force for the Middle East |result = Adopted |image = |caption = }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 340''' was adopted on October 25, 1973, during the [[Yom Kippur War]]. It was passed after the Security Council was informed of the apparent failure of [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 338|UNSCR 338]] and [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 339|UNSCR 339]] to end the fighting.
In UNSCR 340, the Council demanded that the belligerent parties cease fire immediately and completely, and return to the positions occupied by them at 1650 [[Greenwich Mean Time|GMT]] on 22 October 1973.
The Council also
* Requested the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] to increase the number of United Nations military observers on both sides of the cease-fire lines. * Set up a [[United Nations Emergency Force]] to be composed of personnel drawn from UN member states except [[United Nations Security Council#Permanent members|the permanent members of the Security Council]]. * Requested the Secretary-General to report back within 24 hours on these two provisions. * Requested the Secretary-General report back on a continuing basis on the implementation of this resolution, as well as 338 and 339, and requested all member states to co-operate fully in the implementation of these resolutions.
The resolution was adopted with 14 votes to none. The [[People's Republic of China]] did not vote or formally abstain.
